You can install the slackware packages you need in common/initrd_overlay
and kernel specific stuff like modules or startup scripts in ./initrd_overlay

Use export ROOT=<initrd_overlay> before installing slackware packages with
pkgtools or the netinstallpkg command in /pxe/bin

Run "make overlay image" after modifying "initrd_overlay" content

The modules you install in ./lib/modules/<kernel-version> will be updated when
you run make or "make initrd overlay image" again
